====== ========
socket examples
====== ========

Example programs for posix-socket.
==================================
If the pure-posix was not isntalled they can be executed using
the make commands described below. Otherwise they can be executed
using ``pure <program name>``

socket_server.pure
==================

Opens a TCP socket at port 5000 on the loopback interface and
listens and prints out lines received.
The program can be executed using ``make client``

socket_client.pure
==================

Opens a TCP socket and connect to a server listening at port 5000,
writes 10 lines of text over the socket.
The program can be executed using ``make client``


